urls.title: They're Back - Plastic Fragments Washed Up on the Beach
urls.description: First seen in autumn 2020, the tiny plastic fragments washed up on the beach are back. Find out why it's a problem, with Visit Fylde Coast.

tweets.text:
Over recent days significant quantities of microplastics have washed up on #FyldeCoast beaches 🔴🟠🟡🟢🔵🟣⚪️ 

We're not sure of the source yet, however samples have been taken and the @EnvAgency and local authorities are aware. 

Find out more here --> https://t.co/U9LDDCb3Jq

@mynci_fool @AbrehartEco @ursula_juta @N_Rivers_Trust I hope this wasn’t the monster Pike 29 June 20 😭the pollution was reported as agricultural runoff and is being investigated by the @EnvAgencyAnglia

tweets.text: We are aware of a pollution incident on the River Frome, Somerset and have staff on site investigating. Mitigation measures will be put in place once the cause and extent of the pollution has been established.

@EnvAgencySE @Thames21 Reports are coming in of bulldozers taking out 200m of hedgerow along the Quaggy between Weigall Rd and Manor Way, close to the EA compound. Saddening when you imagine how hard we try and encourage wildlife along the river generally. @qwag

A section of path in front of Almery Terrace will be closed from 8am to 5pm, Monday to Friday, from today until 18 December.

This closure is for us to lift the glass panels into the gardens of Almery Terrace for our flood wall.

Please see the image for alternate routes. https://t.co/0JiAFf6zJG

@Mr_ian_B @campbellar @DawlishWarrenGC @EnvAgencySW Hi Ian, without the Warren tides would be significantly higher on the Exe and increase risk if flooding in Exeter, Topsham etc. Also a breach would impact the mudflats and other key habitats. More info here https://t.co/XlR7XszCl5
@campbellar @WarrenBirding @DawlishWarrenGC @EnvAgencySW Can you explain why they are vital please?

@campbellar @DawlishWarrenGC @EnvAgencySW That's serious in terms of sea defence as we enter the winter storm season but the real question is why did the very expensive new sea defences fail so spectacularly?

Into Lockdown but work continues apace on gauge refurbishment at Puslinch on the River Yealm.  @EnvAgencySW @DCfieldteamsEA  pulling out all the stops with some much needed TLC and improvements to keep the public safe.  Thanks @paulblackler for the update! https://t.co/xOg51FuMNv
@EnvAgency @BaberghDistrict What’s being done about the ‘contamination’ at Cattawade ? It’s been 3 weeks, 000’s of dead fish and surface algae still very thick ?😡🤷🏼‍♂️ https://t.co/NvjDY7ieDu

Yesterday we went to one our Carbon Landscape reserves, Bickershaw Country Park to look at the recent restoration works & we certainly picked the perfect day. Not only is the site looking amazing but you just can’t beat that autumn gold hour ☀️ What an inspirational place! https://t.co/0I71zrNVb4
@MariaHerlihyEA @EnvAgencySE @MarkHill03 @wifo_ea @sarahchareEA @TobyWillisonEA Who would deal with this please? It would be helpful to know for the future. Many thanks.

Please visit responsibly following our visitor guidelines at https://t.co/QlsuvZvH9s
